Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setFlipping(25.10)                                          setFlipping(25.10)

Name
       setFlipping  -  Specifies the orientation of the bottom row in the core
       area

Syntax
        setFlipping

       [-help]

       flip_type

       Specifies the orientation of the bottom row in the core area. The  com-
       mand  recreates  all the floorplan rows. You can use this command after
       importing the design.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information  for  each setFlipping parameter. For a detailed de-
              scription of the command and all of its parameters, use the  man
              command:

              man setFlipping

       <flip_type>
              Specifies the type of orientation.

              * f: Specifies that the first row flips from the bottom up.

              * n: Specifies that no row flipping is done.

              * s: Specifies that the second row flips from the bottom up.

              Tip:  To  get the flipping value set by the setFlipping command,
              use the following:

              dbGet top.fplan.flipRows

              Data_type: string, required

Examples
              * If the existing orientation of the bottom row is  Mx  and  the
                second  row  from  bottom  is  R0,  then the following command
                changes the second row orientation to Mx and changes the  ori-
                entation of the other rows accordingly (Bottom row orientation
                will be R0).

                setFlipping s

              * If the existing orientation of the bottom row is R0 and second
                row  from bottom is Mx, then the following command changes the
                first row orientation to Mx and changes the orientation of the
                other rows accordingly (second  from  bottom  row  orientation
                will be R0):

                setFlipping f

Related Information
              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

